    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nwithout -DCYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS, user defined type will be allocated statically.\r\nthen __Pyx_PyType_Ready() add flag Py_TPFLAGS_HEAPTYPE to it (It's weird, isn't it?).\r\n\r\nUser call PyType_Modified() with this type,  for example, with python 3.12.8, this line:\r\nhttps://github.com/python/cpython/blob/v3.12.8/Objects/typeobject.c#L820\r\ncast type as heap_type\r\n`((PyHeapTypeObject *)type)->_spec_cache.getitem` points to undefined memory.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\r\n# example code\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### OS\n\n_No response_\n\n### Python version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Cython version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
