            "body": "Yes, i want to define a metaclass for my cdef class with cython\r\n\r\nI googled it and finally i got a way which is like:\r\n  1. define a ready_type() c function, in this function I changed its metaclass type and call PyType_Modified()\r\n  2. overwrite macro PyType_Ready to my customized function above.\r\n\r\nThe python generated code is like this:\r\n\r\n#include \"Python.h\"\r\n#include \"my_overwritten_macros_and_fun.h\"\r\n\r\nset_flags()\r\nPyType_Ready(t)         // here is the problem\r\nunset_flags()\r\n\r\nOr if we have canonical way to change metaclass of type?",
